INSERT INTO detailed_blog (blog_id, author, publish_date, detailed_content)
VALUES 
(10, 'Kevin White', '2024-08-24', 'GraphQL is a modern alternative to REST that offers greater flexibility and efficiency in API design. This post begins by explaining how GraphQL allows clients to request exactly the data they need, reducing the amount of data transferred over the network. It also discusses how GraphQL’s single endpoint simplifies API development and maintenance, as all queries and mutations are handled through one URL. The post then explores the basics of defining a schema, creating types, and writing queries and mutations in GraphQL. It also highlights the benefits of GraphQL’s introspection feature, which allows clients to explore the available data and capabilities of an API dynamically. Additionally, the post covers how to handle complex queries with nested data and how to implement pagination in GraphQL. By the end of this post, readers will understand the key advantages of GraphQL and how to get started with building their own GraphQL APIs.');
